character_name: Frodo Baggins: A young hobbit who continues his quest to destroy the Ring
Gandalf the White: An Istari wizard who travels to aid the Men of Gondor
Aragorn Elessar: A Dúnedain ranger who must finally face his destiny as King of Gondor.
Samwise Gamgee: Better known as Sam

Sméagol Trahald / Gollum: A wretched and treacherous creature who was once one of the river-folk (an extinct race of hobbits) and now guides Frodo and Sam into Mordor. The first scene in the film portrays him in his former life as Sméagol
Peregrin Took: Better known as Pippin
Meriadoc Brandybuck: Better known as Merry
Gimli: A dwarf warrior and companion to Aragorn along with Legolas.
Legolas Greenleaf: An elven prince of Mirkwood and skilled archer who aids Aragorn in his quest to reclaim the throne.
Théoden: The King of Rohan who
Éowyn: Théoden's niece
Faramir: A son of the Stewards of Gondor and head of the Gondorian Rangers defending Osgiliath
Éomer: Éowyn's brother
Elrond: The Elven-King of Rivendell who must convince Aragorn to take up the throne.
Arwen Undómiel: Elrond's daughter and Aragorn's true love
Galadriel: The Elven-Queen of Lothlórien who is aware the time of the elves is at an end.
Denethor: The Steward of Gondor and father of Faramir and Boromir
Bilbo Baggins: Frodo's elderly uncle
Boromir: Faramir's brother and a fallen companion of Aragorn
Celeborn the Wise: The Elven-King of Lothlórien.
Witch-King: The lord of the Nazgûl
Déagol Nahald: Sméagol's cousin
Saruman the White: An Istari wizard
Gríma Wormtongue: Saruman's sycophantic
The Mouth of Sauron: Sauron's ambassador at the Black Gate.
